    "Here Dom(C t) = {s ∈ S | C t (s) ̸ = ∅} is a domain of the controller and the following true; if C t is a safety controller, s.t.",
    "Dom(C t) ̸ = ∅, then any controlled trajectory started at Dom(C 0) never violates the safety requirements.",
    "There are multiple ways to design such a controller C t for different tasks [19], [20]; however, this topic is out of the scope of this paper.",
    "We assume that a fallback safety controller is provided.Let at the moment t an agent be in a state s t and follow a policy π.",
    "We say that a ∈ Enab π (s t) iff the agent may take an action a ∈ A(s t) (even with a probability of zero).Definition 4.3: A policy π is verified safe at state s t (w.r.t a safety controller C t) iff F (s, a) ⊆ Dom(C t+1) for all a ∈ Enab π (s t)."
